Dorsal view: Sutures between the different bones are not apparent. The frontal crests are low, especially anteriorly. They converge posteriorly, but do not fuse to form a sagittal crest. Following this, the crests diverge to define the ‘interparietal triangle’ ( Barone, 1966 ; see also
de Bonis et al ., 1995
), but because the superior part of the occiput is broken we cannot determine its orientation. The braincase is tubular.
